RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO ROOM SCHOOL took a quick lead and raced clear toward the inside, came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn at the rail and was kept alert through the stretch. ROCKING TO HOME chased, raced two deep on the turn and dueled through the stretch to take the nod for second. JUST A FLIRT gave chase through the backstretch, raced three wide on the turn but missed the nod in the stretch duel for second. NICE BUT NAUGHTY chased inside, rounded the turn near the rail then flattened toward mid-stretch. BOBBYS CASE LOAD came away awkwardly then picked up the chase outside, raced in the four path on the turn but showed little more. YDOUHAVETOBESOMEAN saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Two Room School
ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,rated clear inside,pressured 5/16,rail turn,kept alert

ENTRY.NAME: Bobbys Case Load
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward break,chased outside,4p turn,little in lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ATLANTIC VAQUERO accelerated to the front approaching the five sixteenths pole and drew clear past the pole, widened at the rail on the turn and was steadily handled through the lane. SWIFT DANCER contested the early pace then gave chase toward the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn off the rail and just lasted for second. BUMPY LANDING chased, raced near the rail on the turn, finished evenly and just missed second. MO EH HENNESSY contested the early pace, raced near the rail on the turn then flattened inside the eighth pole. ALWAYS GET REVENGE hit the gate at the break, gave chase outside and rounded the turn about the four path. BROKESTER chased outside, raced in the six path on the turn, showed little in the lane and was vanned off. ARTHUR S GOLD raced well back.

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Eh Hennessy
ENTRY.OWNER: Fanelli John and Longball Stables LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Brokester
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside,6p turn,little in lane,vanned off

ENTRY.OWNER: Aguilar Jose B and Gallegos Jose M

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Claiming Purse 13100. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPECTACULO stalked off the rail then took the nod two deep approaching the five sixteenths pole, drew clear midway on the far turn and was steadily handled in the lane. AIR MEDAL saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and finished well to clear second later yards. CHASE LIL ME saved ground off the pace on the opening turn, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, angled to about the five path leaving the turn and finished evenly to take third later yards. CHIPPEWA'S CASTLE veered in at the break and set the early pace inside, was met toward the five sixteenths pole, gave chase from that point but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and flattened stride in the lane. MADDEYE MOODY rated close to the early pace off the rail, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole but weakened in the four path on the far turn. MASTER YOO was shut off at the break and rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole then flattened at the rail on the far turn. PONTICELLO was shuffled back early, raced in the three path on the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. The Stewards reviewed then dis-allowed a claim of foul against the rider of Spectaculo for alleged interference on the far turn, lodged by the rider of Chippewa's Castle. In addition, this race was hand timed.

ENTRY.NAME: Chase Lil Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 7/16,rail far turn,even finish,up 3rd late

ENTRY.NAME: Maddeye Moody
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close off rail,chased 3/8,weakened 4p far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Ponticello
ENTRY.OWNER: Sperling Nancie S and Racanelli Mark Joseph

ENTRY.NAME: Master Yoo
ENTRY.COMMENT: shut off break,4p 1st turn,chased 3/8,flattened rail far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Chippewa's Castle
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered in break,early lead inside,met 5/16,rail turn,flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Spectaculo
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked,nod 2d near 5/16,clear mid turn,steadily handled lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TREASURER raced with the early pace inside but dropped back and stalked into the backstretch, gave chase from the three eighths pole, took the nod two deep midway on the far turn, edged clear approaching the head of the lane and held well under steady handling. ZIGGY STARDUST raced with the early pace two deep but drew clear nearing the half mile pole, came under pressure leaving the three eighths, was met at the rail midway on the far turn, dropped back toward the head of the lane and settled for second best. MOON FALL stalked from the three path, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and raced two deep on the far turn, then dueled through the stretch for third. BAD LINEAGE veered out at the break then saved ground, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. KING OF LUCK was shuffled back at the start then saved ground, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. COURT TUDOR showed little response through the backstretch. TO THE TOP hit the gate and made contact with. SENZA STRIKE leaving the gate, rounded the turn about the three path and never factored. The latter was bumped leaving the gate and saved ground racing well back. This race was hand timed.

ENTRY.NAME: Treasurer
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace inside,stalked 1/2,chased 3/8,nod mid turn,held well

ENTRY.NAME: King of Luck
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: shuffled back start,saved ground,chased 7/16,rail turn,empty lane

ENTRY.NAME: Ziggy Stardust
ENTRY.COMMENT: w/pace 2d,clear near 1/2,met rail mid turn,settled 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOPWATCHSONNY pressured the pace two deep and raced at even terms through the turn, dug in determinedly from the head of the lane and took the nod in the final strides. MANAGED MISCHIEF took the lead at the rail nearing the three eighths pole and set a pressured pace, contested even terms through the turn, dug in gamely leaving the turn but was nipped in the final strides. TAKE CHARGE LISA engaged in close chase through the backstretch, contested at even terms three wide on the turn but dropped back into the lane and relented the final sixteenth. HOWSAFEAREMYCOLORS gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. BESTLA chased inside, rounded the turn near the rail, eased outward leaving the turn and ran evenly through the stretch. BRANDYURAFINEGIRL chased, raced three wide on the turn, angled out leaving the turn and flattened stride widest. GREAT DEVOTION gave chase four wide then weakened leaving the turn. BRASS BAND chased through the backstretch, raced two deep on the turn, was carried out entering the stretch and weakened. TWIN CAUSE and FLAT OUT COOL were not factors.

ENTRY.NAME: Managed Mischief
ENTRY.COMMENT: up rail 3/8,set pressured pace,even terms turn,nipped final strds

ENTRY.NAME: Brass Band
ENTRY.OWNER: Carrington Dale and Agostini Arthur O

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 39. Maiden Claiming Purse 14400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ODINA took the lead leaving the three quarter pole and rated the pace, widened at the rail on the far turn and was kept sharp through the stretch. JUJU ON DA BEAT saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and settled for second best. BANK CARD became a bit anxious in the gate then settled off the rail, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and came along for third inside the eighth pole. TRACE ESTATE raced well off the pace inside on the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and could only improve her position. LADY GANGSTER exchanged contact with Isle Be There leaving the gate then stalked from the three path, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and showed little in the lane. PRETTY CASTLE rounded the opening turn about the three path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but flattened off the rail on the far turn. ISLE BE THERE exchanged contact with Lady Gangster leaving the gate, rounded the first turn in the six path, raced outside into the backstretch and showed little response. OK EMILY was not a factor. GATTOLOTTASPARKLE saved ground on the first turn and faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Trace Estate
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace inside,chased 3/8,rail far turn,improved position

ENTRY.NAME: Bank Card
ENTRY.COMMENT: anxious in gate,off rail,chased 7/16,rail far turn,along 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Odina
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace,widened rail far turn,kept sharp lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 1 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHROMATIC LASS had the lead in the front stretch then stalked into the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, took over two deep midway on the far turn, was steadily handled in the upper stretch but widened of her own initiative the final sixteenth. BARBERS POINT stalked from the three path the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in range of the leader in the three path of the far turn and came along for second later yards. TIMETOGETUP rated the pace inside, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, was met at the rail midway on the far turn and weakened the final sixteenth. MISS LAUREN lunged from the gate then saved ground, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn, eased out leaving the turn but showed little more. RIVER REWARDS RVF raced boxed at the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and weakened in the lane. BREADMAN'S ROSEBUD rounded the first turn in the two and three paths and showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Timetogetup
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated early pace,pressured near 1/4,met mid turn,weaken 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGGIE'S GIRL took the lead at the seven sixteenths pole and rated a clear pace, was urged away at the rail on the turn then kept alert through the stretch. LIL BOUGIE ran loose in the post parade then gave chase through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and settled for second best. CARMELIZED exchanged contact with Wooden Ships leaving the gate, gave chase inside and raced at the rail on the turn, then relented in the stretch duel for second. POLISH THE DIAMOND chased the early pace toward the outside, rounded the turn about the four path then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. JUBA'S PARADE broke inward and hit the gate then gave chase, rounded the turn about the six path and passed rivals outside. CANDY LOVES HONEY was bumped inward and into Wooden Ships leaving the gate then gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn, eased outward leaving the turn but showed little further. SMOKIN LADY had a brief early lead then gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path of the turn and weakened in the lane. WOODEN SHIPS was bumped then jostled at the break, gave chase through the backstretch, raced two deep on the turn and weakened in the stretch. FLATTERING WAY saved ground. UNALTERED gave chase outside and rounded the turn about the seven path.

ENTRY.NAME: Juba's Parade
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in,hit gate,chased,6p turn,passed rivals outside

ENTRY.NAME: Maggie's Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated clear,urged away rail turn,kept alert lane
